			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Now isn't this the million dollar question. I think a lot of people want to know the answer to this one. I personally get so tired of setting around for hours waiting for that right tank or cleric to come along. Then you get these picky people. Well, I will group with you but you have to do it at this LDON camp or I am not coming. For crying out loud I just want EXP!
<br />

<br />
I get so tired of having to beg a cleric or tank to come and group with me. LDON has made it almost impossible to do anything without a good tank and a good healer at the high end. That is great for the warriors pallies and SK's but it messes over a lot of the other classes in the game. 
<br />

<br />
 I am not saying all clerics and warriors are like this. Most of the ones I have met are very friend and you can get along with them very well but if eq wants to make this a group game make the classes (Even at high end) interchangable to a point. I mean you have to have a tank, Cleric, and some kind of slower to do an LDON that is 58+. Sometimes you can get away with a monk tanking  or a druid/shaman for healer but you have to be very careful with that. 
<br />

<br />
I wish SoE would give back my mages ability to solo mobs. I do not want the See all, end all of Exp in the game from it but it would be nice to be able to go and still be able to do it during those times when you just can not find a group. Will SoE put this ability back in the game for mages? I doubt it but I would like to know why they are so against soloing. 
<br />

<br />
Ravenspire Merquise-lvl 62 Arch Mage of Povar and Proud member of Asatru</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
