				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Money Money Money..
<br />

<br />
Ok if that is the goal..
<br />

<br />
When players are online they are using electricity and bandwidth.
<br />

<br />
Lets do the math.. 14.00 per month (easier math)
<br />

<br />
for every hour of play it costs you .02 in costs.
<br />

<br />
1. player who plays 2 hours per day.. 30 days per month = 60 hours.  Cost to maintain this player is 1.20 per month... Profit = 12.80.
<br />

<br />
2. Player who plays 10 hours per day.. 30 days per month 300 hours.
<br />
this player costs you 6.00... profit = 8.00.
<br />

<br />
Ok, if a player takes an hour every day to get a group it costs SoE 30 hours of wasted time = 0.60 per month of wasted time.  Along with that a player knows they are wasting their time also.  The less time a player is online is the more money a company profits. Less bandwith and electricity are used.  This will make the green party happy also.
<br />

<br />
Solo experience makes SENSE. Less wait time for a group.
<br />

<br />
For all those who say that grouping makes more money, you are flat out wrong.
<br />

<br />
Ryan, your looking for the hard sell? Your bean counters will understand what I just wrote from a business standpoint.<br />_________________<br />Genu
