				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think the comunity is about evenly split on the subject.
<br />

<br />
There are alot of good ideas and reasons expressed in this thread both for and against solo.
<br />

<br />
But all those that want to solo dont want to do it ALL the time, but we want the option to do it and do it well.  We (I include myself) are the casual player who wants to play now and then.  I dont have the time for a raiding guild that hunts 3x a week.  I travel and cannot always be comitted.
<br />

<br />
I have seen several 'generations' come and go thru eq since I started, but the casual players like myself usally stick around a long time.  And those in heavly raiding guilds get burned out after months or years of constant raids.
<br />

<br />
Ryan, the hard sell to help us solo.
<br />

<br />
1. Casual players make EQ more profit, less content is needed and not online as much.
<br />

<br />
2. The casual player wants to solo when we are online because we can just go some where to play.
<br />

<br />
3. Magicians were and STILL are sold as being able to solo (make a magician and read the information about them).
<br />

<br />
I personaly dont want to make 100% the experince I would make in a group, but 80% would be good in Teir 2 places.<br />_________________<br />Genu
