				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think Sony, as well as many of you, should consider that a soloing player in a MMORPG is not truely playing by himself.  One viewpoint is that playing the game with other players means raiding/grouping.  Another viewpoint could be that playing the game with other players means doing many things on your own, while still interacting with other players when you chose to.
<br />

<br />
Even when I'm <span style="font-weight: bold">soloing</span>, it's hardly playing <span style="font-weight: bold">Everquest by myself</span>.  Quite the contrary...  When I'm soloing I'm normally chatting with other online friends, working on some quest that my guild needs me to do (when I was working on my Vex Thal key, soloing for a piece that would allow me to raid with lots of people).  Some of the last few AA I have bought with exp earned from soloing were spent on Spell Casting Subtlety.  I sure as hell don't need that for soloing, only for not taking aggro when raiding.
<br />

<br />
So next time, before many of you quote Everquest to be a MMORPG and state soloing does not fit the description, perhaps you should rethink what soloing <span style="font-weight: bold">TRUELY </span>means.  When I play Legend of Zelda, or Metroid on my latest nintendo system, I'm soloing.  In Everquest, I have never truely <span style="text-decoration: underline">soloed </span>for as long as I have played.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Eandori Raintree</a></b>
